The paper deals with the problem of sorting a sequence of elements, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The paper proposes a new sorting algorithm called QuickMergesort and compares it with state-of-the-art library implementations. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of algorithms (cs.AL), data structures (cs.DS), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the number of comparisons required for sorting, which suggests that it may belong to the category of information theory (cs.IT) or numerical analysis (cs.NA).
